      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating Kokoro into Your API Stack"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Start by provisioning Kokoro via its API gateway, using API keys for authentication. Implement retry logic with exponential backoff for transient errors, and leverage webhooks for asynchronous processing. For high availability, deploy across multiple regions with load balancers. Use versioned endpoints to manage model updates without downtime, and integrate logging with tools like Prometheus for real-time monitoring."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimizing for Production Deployment"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimize Kokoro by tuning batch sizes based on traffic patterns—smaller batches for low-latency needs, larger for throughput. Enable caching for repeated queries using Redis or similar systems. Set up auto-scaling policies tied to CPU/memory thresholds, and conduct regular health checks. Finally, profile API responses to identify bottlenecks, and consider edge deployments for reduced latency in global applications."
          }
        ]
      }
